   impacted by the changing climate. It depicts a family of Inuit,
   commonly referred to as Eskimos, in Uummannaq. The name Eskimos comes
   from the word "Eskimautik", which means "Those who eat raw meat".
   Traditional dress of Polar bear, seal skin, boots, and fur-lined
   coverings have to help Inuit people to survive some of Earth’s coldest
   weather for centuries. Without sea ice, seals cannot build ledges on
   which to rest, eat and bear their pups; walruses cannot find refuge on
   drift ice to rest, and digest their meals; polar bears cannot catch
   seals; hunters cannot travel in dog sled. arctic biologists say that
   the entire ecosystem is about to collapse. Photo : Stanley Greene
   (@noorimages). Taken on October 21, 2009.————————————————————————
